metadata.name: Allégories booléennes #483
metadata.description:
"Allégories booléennes" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at PARIS+ par Art Basel

This work is a continuation of research around the intersections of shapes that I have been exploring for a while. I wonder about the way in which they make it possible to bring out new compositions from superpositions of shapes that could initially represent a real disorder.

Controls:
• "a": Play the animation
• "s": Export the image (default 2160 × 3840px PNG)
• "h": Change export settings to high resolution (then press "s" to export a 6480 ×11520px PNG)
• "m": Change export settings to medium resolution (then press "s" to export a 4320 × 7680px PNG)
• "n": Back to 2160 × 3840px

Artwork by Julien Espagnon, 2022.

metadata.name: Pixel Babies #25
metadata.description:
Mother's favourite babies :)
90k possible variations 

Details:

Backgrounds: - babyblue / blue / orange / pink / playground(8%)
Skincolours: - White / Dark / Alien(4%)
Diaper: - babyblue / blue / pink / purple / white
Dummy: - babyblue / blue / pink / purple / white
Toy: - no toy(85%) / bucket(5%) / stuffed animal(5%) / robot(5%)
Headwear: - bald / blonde hair long / blonde hair short / braids / brown curl / brown hair / cap / golden curl / ribbon / waves



thanks for your support <3

metadata.name: Different Intersections - Iteration 4 #243
metadata.description:
This is the culmination of a series of iterations

____ - Iteration 1
____ - Iteration 2
____ - Iteration 3

The iterations were released under the pseudonym Extracurricular Activities.

The algorithmic theme of the iterations was extensive usage of boolean operations (intersection and difference) on polygons to derive interesting composite shapes.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

metadata.name: Aliens #76
metadata.description:
"Aliens" is a collection derivated from "The Odd One Out" collection where you can see up close one of these some of its aliens:
- Longlorb: A slug-alien, not the most intelligent
- Skidle: A big mouth alien
- Trunglute: A mutated tree-alien
- Penclope: A cyclope alien with five tentacles
- NFT-Rex: An alien that may come from the dinoverse
- Blurp: An alien that will eat everything
- Booz: The main protagonist of the crowd, the one that needs to be find out

---------- CONTROLS -----------
- Double-click on the token to zoom into the picture (on Smartphone you can zoom normally)
- Right-click on the token to trigger download options (4 download options are available, low-res, normal-res, high-res and SVG), if you want to download a very high-fidelity of your token, I recommend the SVG option (Which you can then convert into PNG on various websites).
